import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['price'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Stock Prices')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Stock Prices')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of stock prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    avg_prices = data.groupby('symbol')['price'].mean()
    ax = avg_prices.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange', 'green', 'red', 'purple'])
    
    plt.title('What is the average price of each stock symbol?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Stock Symbol')
    plt.ylabel('Average Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Average Price'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    for symbol in data['symbol'].unique():
        symbol_data = data[data['symbol'] == symbol]
        ax.plot(symbol_data['date'], symbol_data['price'], label=symbol)
    
    ax.set_title('How has the price of each stock symbol changed over time?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    unique_symbols_by_date = data.groupby('date')['symbol'].nunique()
    max_unique_symbols = unique_symbols_by_date.max()
    
    plt.hist(unique_symbols_by_date, bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.axvline(max_unique_symbols, color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Max: {max_unique_symbols:.2f}')
    
    plt.xlabel('Number of Unique Stock Symbols')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of unique stock symbols per date?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
